  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H SF10 workload dominated by massive 60M-row lineitem fact table scanned 5x across Q1/Q3/Q6/Q9/Q18. Critical bottlenecks: (1) Q1 full scan with 10-way GROUP BY aggregation (6 groups output), (2) Q3 multi-table join on selective date predicates (<5% selectivity), (3) Q9 6-way join requiring both filter pushdown and semi-join on part name. High SIMD/parallelism opportunity on 64-core CPU with AVX-512 support. Key optimizations: (1) vectorized filtered scans for Q1/Q6, (2) bloom filter semi-joins for Q3/Q9, (3) sorted aggregation on low-cardinality GROUP BY keys, (4) parallel hash table construction for multi-table joins."
